ad PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533772\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533772\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xlh1665702953434.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xlh1665702953434.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xlh1665702953434.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xlh1665702953434\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Table Management on ODBC\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Tables are created on the fly, or by SQL scripts generated by the Create Table\n      facility.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__p_d54797e1_d54798e1_d54799e1\"> When you first attempt to access a table, Uniface needs\n         to know if it exists. If the table does not exist, Uniface creates and indexes it, using\n         the information from the application model. Taking into account the value of the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"auj1665702731375.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/auj1665702731375.html\" title=\"Specify the syntax of indexes and primary keys.\">key syntax</a> connector option, the table is created as follows:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__li_d25268e1_d25269e1_d25270e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">create table</code> statement is issued. The primary key constraint is created within table creation.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__li_d25271e1_d25272e1_d25273e1\">Indexes are created with the <code class=\"ph codeph\">create index</code> statement.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__section_fby_ytm_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d144784e76\">Overflow Tables</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__p_d54803e1_d54804e1_d54805e1\">Overflow tables can be created on the fly. Entities\n            that contain one of the following Uniface packing codes require both a standard table\n            and an overflow table, if the data source does not support SQL_LONGVARCHAR or\n            SQL_LONGVARBINARY:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__ul_k2b_ztm_jcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__li_d25274e1_d25275e1_d25276e1\">C* </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__li_d25277e1_d25278e1_d25279e1\">VC* </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__li_d25280e1_d25281e1_d25282e1\">U* </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__li_d25283e1_d25284e1_d25285e1\">VU* </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__li_d25286e1_d25287e1_d25288e1\">S* </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__li_d25289e1_d25290e1_d25291e1\">VS* </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__li_d25292e1_d25293e1_d25294e1\">R* </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__li_d25295e1_d25296e1_d25297e1\">VR* </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__p_d54806e1_d54807e1_d54808e1\">An overflow table contains the primary key from the\n            base table, and the overflow information from the field which causes the overflow table.\n            The name for an overflow table consists of the same name as the entity name with the\n            prefix ‘<code class=\"ph codeph\">o</code>’ (lower case) or ‘<code class=\"ph codeph\">O</code>’ (upper case), depending\n            on the connector option <code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rmo1665702729638.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rmo1665702729638.html\" title=\"Case for table and column names\">identifier case</a>\n</code> (or <code class=\"ph codeph\">id case</code>).</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xlh1665702953434__note_p2b_ztm_jcc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The overflow mechanism is a technical encoding for larger amounts of data, and is not transparent to other applications.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rvk1665702925977.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Overflow Tables</a><p>DBMSs may impose upper limits to the number of fields in a table, the length of a field, and the length of a record. Some DBMSs do not support variable-length fields with a high maximum length. To overcome these limitations, Uniface provides an overflow mechanism, in which data that is represented as a single modeled entity is automatically split into two tables—the base table and an overflow table.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533772\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533772\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Table Management on ODBC Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Table Management on ODBC Tables are created on the fly, or by SQL scripts generated by the Create Table facility. When you first attempt to access a table, Uniface needs to know if it exists. If the table does not exist, Uniface creates and indexes it, using the information from the application model. Taking into account the value of the key syntax connector option, the table is created as follows: The create table statement is issued. The primary key constraint is created within table creation. Indexes are created with the create index statement. Overflow Tables Overflow tables can be created on the fly. Entities that contain one of the following Uniface packing codes require both a standard table and an overflow table, if the data source does not support SQL_LONGVARCHAR or SQL_LONGVARBINARY: C* VC* U* VU* S* VS* R* VR* An overflow table contains the primary key from the base table, and the overflow information from the field which causes the overflow table. The name for an overflow table consists of the same name as the entity name with the prefix ‘ o ’ (lower case) or ‘ O ’ (upper case), depending on the connector option identifier case (or id case ). Note: The overflow mechanism is a technical encoding for larger amounts of data, and is not transparent to other applications. Related Links Overflow Tables DBMSs may impose upper limits to the number of fields in a table, the length of a field, and the length of a record. Some DBMSs do not support variable-length fields with a high maximum length. To overcome these limitations, Uniface provides an overflow mechanism, in which data that is represented as a single modeled entity is automatically split into two tables—the base table and an overflow table. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}